# ⠋⠇⠁⠗⠑  flare

**Terminal graphics with unicode, braille, color, and a full animation studio.**

Flare renders 2-D shapes, 3-D scenes, and keyframe animations directly in your terminal using braille, block elements, ASCII ramps, or any character you can type. Every pixel supports ANSI true-color. The `flare.studio` sublibrary gives you a Moon Animator-style timeline with easing, camera animation, layers, and multi-track playback.

```
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⣠⣴⣶⣷⣶⣶⣤⡀⠀⠀⣠⣴⣶⣷⣶⣦⡀⠀
⠀⠀⢸⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⠀⢸⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⠀
⠀⠀⠈⠻⢿⣿⣿⣿⡿⠟⠁⠀⠈⠻⢿⣿⣿⣿⡿⠋⠀
```

---

## Quick Install

```bash
# Core (zero dependencies)
pip install flare-gfx

# With image support
pip install "flare-gfx[image]"

# From source
git clone https://github.com/lowercasetoast/flare
cd flare
pip install -e .
```

---

## 30-Second Demo

```python
import flare
from flare.core import Color

c = flare.Canvas(120, 60)
flare.draw_circle(c, 30, 30, 20, filled=True, color=Color.CYAN)
flare.draw_rect(c, 60, 15, 40, 30, filled=True, color=Color.MAGENTA)
flare.draw_gradient_rect(c, 0, 50, 120, 10, Color.RED, Color.BLUE)
flare.draw_text(c, 5, 5, "FLARE", color=Color.YELLOW)
c.show()
```

### Animation studio

```python
from flare.studio import Studio, Easing
from flare.core import Color

s = Studio(120, 60, fps=24)

ball = s.add_track("ball", "circle2d")
ball.keyframe(0,  x=10,  y=30, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.RED)
ball.keyframe(48, x=110, y=30, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.BLUE,
              easing=Easing.EASE_IN_OUT_BOUNCE)

s.play()
```

