## Canvas

### `Canvas(width, height, charset='braille', color=True, bg=None)`

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `width` | `int` | Pixel width |
| `height` | `int` | Pixel height |
| `charset` | `str` | `'braille'` (default), `'block'`, or a custom ramp string |
| `color` | `bool` | Enable ANSI true-color (default `True`) |
| `bg` | `Color` | Background color |

```python
c = flare.Canvas(120, 60)                        # braille + color
c = flare.Canvas(80, 40, charset='block')        # block elements
c = flare.Canvas(80, 40, charset=' .:-=+*#%@')  # ASCII ramp
c = flare.Canvas(80, 40, color=False)            # no color
```

### Canvas methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `set_pixel(x, y, value=1.0, color=None)` | Set a single pixel |
| `get_pixel(x, y)` | Read pixel brightness |
| `get_pixel_color(x, y)` | Read pixel color |
| `set_color(color)` | Set the active drawing color |
| `clear()` | Reset all pixels to 0 |
| `render()` | Return canvas as a multi-line string |
| `show()` | Print the canvas |
| `add_group(name, group)` | Register a named Group |
| `get_group(name)` | Retrieve a group by name |
| `draw_group(name)` | Draw a named group |
| `draw_all()` | Draw all registered groups |

---

## Color

### `Color(r, g, b)`

```python
from flare.core import Color

Color(255, 60, 60)             # from RGB
Color.from_hex("#00ffcc")      # from hex
Color.from_hsv(270, 1.0, 1.0) # from HSV (h=0-360, s/v=0-1)
Color.RED.lerp(Color.BLUE, 0.5)# interpolate -> purple
```

### Built-in constants

`Color.RED` `Color.GREEN` `Color.BLUE` `Color.WHITE` `Color.BLACK`
`Color.YELLOW` `Color.CYAN` `Color.MAGENTA` `Color.ORANGE` `Color.PINK`

### Color methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Color(r, g, b)` | RGB 0–255 |
| `Color.from_hex(s)` | Parse `"#rrggbb"` |
| `Color.from_hsv(h, s, v)` | h=0–360, s/v=0–1 |
| `color.lerp(other, t)` | Interpolate (t=0–1) |
| `color.ansi_fg()` | ANSI foreground escape string |
| `color.ansi_bg()` | ANSI background escape string |

---

## Drawing Functions

All accept `canvas` as first arg and optional `color=` parameter.

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `draw_pixel(canvas, x, y, value=1.0, color=None)` | Single pixel |
| `draw_line(canvas, x0, y0, x1, y1, value=1.0, color=None)` | Bresenham line |
| `draw_rect(canvas, x, y, w, h, filled=False, value=1.0, color=None)` | Rectangle |
| `draw_circle(canvas, cx, cy, radius, filled=False, value=1.0, color=None)` | Circle |
| `draw_ellipse(canvas, cx, cy, rx, ry, filled=False, value=1.0, color=None)` | Ellipse |
| `draw_triangle(canvas, x0,y0, x1,y1, x2,y2, filled=False, value=1.0, color=None)` | Triangle |
| `draw_polygon(canvas, points, filled=False, value=1.0, color=None)` | Polygon |
| `draw_text(canvas, x, y, text, color=None)` | 3×5 bitmap text |
| `draw_bezier(canvas, points, steps=200, value=1.0, color=None)` | Bézier curve |
| `draw_gradient_rect(canvas, x, y, w, h, color_a, color_b, direction='horizontal')` | Gradient fill |

```python
flare.draw_circle(c, 60, 30, 20, filled=True, color=Color.CYAN)
flare.draw_gradient_rect(c, 0, 0, 120, 10, Color.RED, Color.BLUE)
flare.draw_text(c, 10, 5, "HELLO WORLD", color=Color.YELLOW)
flare.draw_bezier(c, [(10,50),(40,5),(80,50),(110,5)], color=Color.MAGENTA)
```

---

## Groups & Transforms

```python
from flare.groups import Group, Shape, Transform

g = flare.Group("ships")
g.add(Shape(my_draw_fn, name="hero"))
g.translate(20, 10).rotate(45).scale(2)
g.draw(canvas)

# Register on canvas by name
canvas.add_group("ships", g)
canvas.draw_group("ships")
canvas.draw_all()
```

### Group methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `g.add(child)` | Add Shape or nested Group |
| `g.remove(child)` | Remove a child |
| `g.clear()` | Remove all children |
| `g.get_child(name)` | Find child by name |
| `g.translate(dx, dy)` | Shift the group |
| `g.rotate(angle_deg)` | Rotate CCW |
| `g.scale(sx, sy=None)` | Scale |
| `g.move_to(x, y)` | Set absolute position |
| `g.reset_transform()` | Reset to identity |
| `g.draw(canvas)` | Draw all children |

### Transform

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Transform.identity()` | Identity transform |
| `t.translate(dx, dy)` | New translated transform |
| `t.rotate(angle_deg)` | New rotated transform (CCW) |
| `t.scale(sx, sy=None)` | New scaled transform |
| `t.apply(x, y)` | Transform point → `(x′, y′)` |

---

## Image Conversion

> Requires `pip install "flare-gfx[image]"`

```python
# From file
c = flare.from_file("photo.png", width=120, height=60, dither=True)

# From Pillow Image
from PIL import Image
c = flare.from_pil(Image.open("art.png").rotate(45), width=80)

# From raw pixel grid (2-D list of 0.0–1.0 floats)
c = flare.from_pixels(grid, grayscale=True)
```

| Parameter | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `width/height` | Output size (preserves aspect ratio if only one given) |
| `threshold` | Brightness cutoff for on/off pixels (default 0.5) |
| `invert` | Swap light and dark |
| `dither` | Floyd–Steinberg dithering |
| `grayscale` | Store raw brightness — use with ramp charsets |

---

## 3-D Rendering

No external libraries required. Full perspective pipeline in pure Python.

```python
cam   = flare.Camera(position=(0, 1.5, -5), target=(0,0,0), fov_deg=60)
cube  = flare.make_cube(1.5)
cube.rotate_y(35).rotate_x(20)

scene = flare.Scene(cam)
scene.add(cube)
scene.render_to(canvas)
```

### Camera

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `position` | `(0,0,-5)` | Eye position |
| `target` | `(0,0,0)` | Look-at point |
| `up` | `(0,1,0)` | Up vector |
| `fov_deg` | `60` | Field of view |
| `near/far` | `0.1/1000` | Clip planes |

### Mesh methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `mesh.translate(dx, dy, dz)` | Move in world space |
| `mesh.rotate_x/y/z(deg)` | Rotate around axis |
| `mesh.scale(sx, sy, sz)` | Scale |
| `mesh.reset_transform()` | Reset to identity |

### Built-in mesh factories

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `make_cube(size=1.0)` | Unit cube |
| `make_sphere(radius=1.0, lat=8, lon=12)` | UV sphere |
| `make_plane(w=2.0, h=2.0, nx=4, ny=4)` | Flat XZ grid |

---

## Simple Animation

```python
c    = flare.Canvas(120, 60)
anim = flare.Animation(c, fps=24, clear_mode='inline')

def update(canvas, frame, elapsed):
    flare.draw_circle(canvas, 60, 30, int(10 + 8*math.sin(elapsed*2)),
                      filled=True, color=Color.CYAN)

anim.play(update, duration=10, loop=True)

# Export frames without displaying
rendered = flare.frames(c, update_fn, count=48)
```

---

## Charsets

| Constant | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `BRAILLE` | `'braille'` — 2×4 braille cells (default) |
| `BLOCK` | `'block'` — 2×2 block elements |
| `ASCII_RAMP` | `" .:-=+*#%@"` — 10-level ASCII |
| `EXTENDED_RAMP` | 70-char detailed ASCII ramp |
| `SHADE_RAMP` | `" ░▒▓█"` — unicode shade blocks |
| `DOTS_RAMP` | `" .:;!I#@"` |
| `NUMBERS_RAMP` | `" 123456789"` |
| `HEX_RAMP` | `" 0-9A-F"` |
| `MATRIX_RAMP` | `" 01"` |
| `BRAILLE_RAMP` | All 256 braille code points as grayscale ramp |
| `BOX_DRAWING` | `"─│┌┐└┘├┤┬┴┼"` |
| `ARROWS` | `"←→↑↓↔↕⇐⇒⇑⇓"` |
| `MATH` | `"∑∏∫∂∆∇±×÷≤≥≠≈∞"` |

```python
c = flare.Canvas(80, 40, charset=flare.charsets.SHADE_RAMP)
```

---

## flare.studio — Animation Studio

Import separately — it's a sublibrary:

```python
from flare.studio import Studio, Easing, CameraTrack
```

### Studio

```python
s = Studio(
    canvas_width=120,
    canvas_height=60,
    fps=24,
    charset='braille',
    color=True,
    loop=True,
)
```

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `s.add_track(name, kind, layer=None, draw_fn=None)` | Add an object track |
| `s.add_layer(name)` | Create a layer |
| `s.add_camera(name)` | Create an animated camera |
| `s.set_active_camera(name)` | Choose active camera for 3-D |
| `s.get_track(name)` | Get track by name |
| `s.remove_track(name)` | Remove a track |
| `s.render_frame(frame)` | Render one frame → string |
| `s.play(start, end, loop, clear_mode)` | Play in terminal |
| `s.export_frames(start, end)` | Return all frames as `list[str]` |
| `s.export_gif_frames(path_template)` | Write frames to text files |
| `s.on_pre_frame(fn)` | Hook: `fn(canvas, frame, elapsed)` before draw |
| `s.on_post_frame(fn)` | Hook: `fn(canvas, frame, elapsed)` after draw |
| `s.info()` | Print track/layer summary |
| `s.total_frames` | Last keyframe across all tracks |

### Track & Keyframe

```python
track = s.add_track("ball", "circle2d")

track.keyframe(0,  x=10, y=30, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.RED)
track.keyframe(48, x=110,y=30, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.BLUE,
               easing=Easing.EASE_IN_OUT_BOUNCE)
```

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `track.keyframe(frame, easing=None, **props)` | Add/update keyframe |
| `track.remove_keyframe(frame)` | Remove keyframe |
| `track.clear_keyframes()` | Remove all |
| `track.state_at(frame)` | Interpolated props dict at frame |
| `track.duration` | Last keyframe number |
| `track.visible` | Show/hide bool |

### Easing

25 easing functions — use as attributes or name strings:

```python
track.keyframe(30, x=100, easing=Easing.EASE_OUT_BOUNCE)
track.keyframe(30, x=100, easing="ease_out_bounce")  # same thing
```

| Category | Names |
|----------|-------|
| Basic | `linear`, `step` |
| Quad | `ease_in/out/in_out_quad` |
| Cubic | `ease_in/out/in_out_cubic` |
| Quart | `ease_in/out/in_out_quart` |
| Sine | `ease_in/out/in_out_sine` |
| Expo | `ease_in/out/in_out_expo` |
| Back (overshoot) | `ease_in/out/in_out_back` |
| Elastic (spring) | `ease_in/out/in_out_elastic` |
| Bounce | `ease_in/out/in_out_bounce` |

### Layers

```python
bg = s.add_layer("background")
fg = s.add_layer("foreground")

sky  = s.add_track("sky",  "gradient", layer="background")
hero = s.add_track("hero", "circle2d", layer="foreground")

bg.visible = False  # hide entire layer
```

### CameraTrack

```python
cam = s.add_camera("main")
cam.keyframe(0,  px=0, py=2, pz=-6, tx=0, ty=0, tz=0, fov=60)
cam.keyframe(48, px=3, py=4, pz=-5, fov=45,
             easing=Easing.EASE_IN_OUT_SINE)
```

| Property | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `px, py, pz` | `0, 0, -5` | Camera position |
| `tx, ty, tz` | `0, 0, 0` | Look-at target |
| `fov` | `60` | Field of view (degrees) |
| `roll` | `0` | Camera roll (degrees) |

### 2-D track kinds

| `kind` | Key properties |
|--------|---------------|
| `circle2d` | `x, y, radius, filled, color` |
| `rect2d` | `x, y, w, h, filled, color` |
| `line2d` | `x0, y0, x1, y1, color` |
| `triangle2d` | `x0,y0, x1,y1, x2,y2, filled, color` |
| `ellipse2d` | `x, y, rx, ry, filled, color` |
| `polygon2d` | `points, filled, color` |
| `bezier2d` | `points, steps, color` |
| `text2d` | `x, y, text, color` |
| `pixel` | `x, y, value, color` |
| `gradient` | `x, y, w, h, color_a, color_b, direction` |
| `custom` | calls `draw_fn(canvas, props)` directly |

### 3-D track (`mesh3d`)

| Property | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `mesh` | A `flare.Mesh` object |
| `rx, ry, rz` | Rotation angles (degrees) |
| `tx, ty, tz` | Translation |
| `sx/sy/sz` or `scale` | Scale |
| `color` | Wire color |
| `draw_points` | Also draw vertex dots |

---

## Full Examples

### Bouncing colored ball

```python
from flare.studio import Studio, Easing
from flare.core import Color

s = Studio(120, 60, fps=24)
ball = s.add_track("ball", "circle2d")
ball.keyframe(0,  x=10,  y=50, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.RED)
ball.keyframe(12, x=35,  y=10, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.ORANGE,
              easing=Easing.EASE_OUT_BOUNCE)
ball.keyframe(24, x=60,  y=50, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.YELLOW,
              easing=Easing.EASE_IN_QUAD)
ball.keyframe(36, x=85,  y=10, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.GREEN,
              easing=Easing.EASE_OUT_BOUNCE)
ball.keyframe(48, x=110, y=50, radius=8, filled=True, color=Color.BLUE,
              easing=Easing.EASE_IN_QUAD)
s.play(loop=True)
```

### Animated 3-D cube with camera

```python
from flare.studio import Studio, Easing
from flare.core import Color
import flare

s = Studio(120, 60, fps=24)

cam = s.add_camera("cam")
cam.keyframe(0,  px=0, py=1.5, pz=-5, fov=60)
cam.keyframe(96, px=3, py=3,   pz=-4, fov=50,
             easing=Easing.EASE_IN_OUT_CUBIC)

cube = s.add_track("cube", "mesh3d")
mesh = flare.make_cube(1.5)
cube.keyframe(0,  mesh=mesh, ry=0,   rx=15, color=Color.CYAN)
cube.keyframe(96, mesh=mesh, ry=360, rx=30, color=Color.MAGENTA,
              easing=Easing.LINEAR)
s.play(loop=True)
```

### Custom draw function track

```python
from flare.studio import Studio, Easing
from flare.core import Color
import flare, math

s = Studio(120, 60, fps=24)

def draw_star(canvas, props):
    cx    = int(props.get("x", 60))
    cy    = int(props.get("y", 30))
    r_out = int(props.get("r_outer", 20))
    r_in  = int(props.get("r_inner", 8))
    angle = props.get("angle", 0)
    col   = props.get("color", Color.YELLOW)
    pts   = []
    for i in range(10):
        r = r_out if i % 2 == 0 else r_in
        a = math.pi * i / 5 + math.radians(angle)
        pts.append((int(cx + r * math.cos(a)), int(cy + r * math.sin(a))))
    flare.draw_polygon(canvas, pts, filled=True, color=col)

star = s.add_track("star", "custom", draw_fn=draw_star)
star.keyframe(0,  x=60, y=30, r_outer=20, r_inner=8, angle=0,
              color=Color.YELLOW)
star.keyframe(48, x=60, y=30, r_outer=25, r_inner=10, angle=180,
              color=Color.ORANGE, easing=Easing.EASE_IN_OUT_BACK)
s.play(loop=True)
```

---

## Project Structure

```
flare/
├── flare/
│   ├── __init__.py       Top-level API
│   ├── core.py           Canvas + Color
│   ├── shapes.py         2-D drawing primitives
│   ├── groups.py         Group, Shape, Transform
│   ├── image.py          Image → Canvas conversion (Pillow optional)
│   ├── threed.py         3-D engine: Camera, Mesh, Scene
│   ├── animation.py      Simple Animation loop + frames()
│   ├── charsets.py       Character set constants
│   └── studio/
│       ├── __init__.py   Studio sublibrary public API
│       ├── studio.py     Studio — timeline + playback engine
│       ├── track.py      Track + Keyframe
│       ├── easing.py     25 easing functions
│       ├── objects.py    Obj2D + Obj3D shape renderers
│       └── camera.py     CameraTrack
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
├── pyproject.toml
└── .gitignore
```

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- No runtime dependencies
- Optional: `Pillow >= 9.0` for image conversion
- Terminal with ANSI true-color support recommended (iTerm2, Windows Terminal, most Linux terminals)

